4 hours ago, Pudgemountain said:

I decided to do my own take on Artemis 1 while waiting for Saturday's launch using Benjee10's Orion.

Launch Vehicle SLSS aka Saturn Launch System Stout.

I'm gonna post the rest in Spoilers since I have alot of pictures up this post already lol.

  Reveal hidden contents

After 3 days she finally arrived to the Moon and achieved 15km orbit.

I did not have any probes to drop so I just orbited it for 2 weeks.

The next pics are in a different filter due to how Dark the Vintage filter is.

Rough but safe.

Not gonna lie I was playing "Rooster" by Alice in Chains during launch, don't know why lol.

I'm starting to think all these hybrid rocket designs need their own thread. But will God forgive us?

Direct flight has other advantages: One of the things that hurt Orion and Altiar bad is the abort at anytime requirement which needed significant margins for plane changes to meet up with the Orion for the polar sites that were desired. That is more a question of what sort of orbit you want than efficiency.

And, there are efficiencies of rendezvous.  Remeber that Apollo 13 wouldn't have been a "successful failure" if the LEM hadn't been there as a lifeboat.
